Even playing field for apps + expand FMF matrix + SmartRent risk slide

Three changes from the cofounder review:

1. Even playing field on per-app slides
   - Removed "#N adoption likelihood" rank pills from all 10 app slides
   - Replaced with neutral status descriptors (Live, Built, In dev, Concept,
     Bundle, etc.) so cofounders form their own view from the visual without
     anchoring on the score order
   - Section 4 divider re-titled "The Buffet" with subtitle:
     "All eleven on equal footing. Pick your favorites - the scorecard
     is just one input."
   - Adoption score still shown in the inline stat-row chip on each app
     slide for analytical reference, but no longer the headline

2. Founder-Market Fit matrix expanded to all 11 apps (slide 22)
   - Was: 5 cards (Channel Portal, GTM, DealPayment, Wedding combo, Rehabit)
   - Now: 11 cards, one per app + Life Events Suite as a separate card
   - New compact card design (4-col grid at desktop) with primary fit
     line + secondary fit line + lane note
   - "SR" badge inline on each SmartRent founder mention; gold "Killer fit"
     badge on the 3 strongest team-coverage apps
   - Channel Partner Portal card carries an inline coral risk-flag pointing
     at slide 23 (the new SmartRent slide)

3. NEW SmartRent Considerations slide (slide 23) + supporting doc
   - Comes right after the FMF matrix
   - Cites three handbook clauses verbatim: Section 1.6 Conflicts of Interest,
     Section 1.10 Outside Employment, Section 3.5 Corporate Opportunities
     (Oct 2025 SmartRent Employee Handbook)
   - Per-app risk read: HIGH for Channel Partner Portal (multifamily
     operator surface overlap), LOW for the other 10 apps, DISCLOSE for
     Real Tech Consulting parent
   - Four disposition paths for Channel Portal:
       A. Drop  B. Defer to post-departure
       C. Get SmartRent Legal Department approval (recommended)
       D. Re-scope away from overlap (commercial RE / HOA / hospitality)
   - "What we agree today" operating rules block (no SmartRent customer
     activation, no SmartRent confidential info into Real Tech, NDA
     Section 7 already protects this)
   - Linked supporting doc: legal/SmartRent-considerations.md (full
     handbook citations + per-app risk table + disposition decision tree)

Cross-slide updates:
- Channel Partner Portal app slide now shows inline coral
  "SmartRent risk - see slide 23" warning in the header
- Top 2 Recommended (slide 27): Path A "Give up" line now reads
  "Slower to first revenue + requires SmartRent disposition decision
  (slide 23)"; Path B explicitly notes "No SmartRent overlap risk"
- 05-founder-market-fit.md gets a callout block pointing to the new
  SmartRent considerations doc
- legal/SmartRent-considerations.md (new): 11 sections covering the
  handbook clauses, per-app risk read, four disposition options,
  operating rules, and recommended next steps. Explicitly disclaimed
  as not legal advice; flagged for Tim's counsel review.

CSS additions:
- .fmf-grid + .fmf-card.killer-fit (gold ring, killer-badge)
- .fmf-card .risk-flag (coral chip for the SmartRent warning)
- .layout-considerations + .disposition-grid + .disp-card.recommended
  (the new slide's risk + 4-path disposition layout)
